8. DISCUSSION
================================================================================

8.1 STRENGTHS
✅ High accuracy (87%) with Random Forest
✅ Preserved 100% of data through mean imputation
✅ Explainable predictions (feature importance)
✅ Professional UI with modern aesthetics
✅ Role-based authentication for clinical use
✅ Batch processing capability (100+ patients)
✅ Comprehensive analytics dashboard
✅ Complete documentation (teaching notebook)
✅ Robust evaluation (10-fold cross-validation)
✅ PDF/HTML report generation
✅ No database dependency (simplified architecture)

8.2 LIMITATIONS
❌ Dataset size limited (303 samples)
❌ Binary classification only (no severity levels)
❌ Simple mean imputation (not advanced like MICE)
❌ No real-time EHR integration
❌ Generalizability to other populations unknown
❌ Session-based storage (no persistent database)
❌ English language interface only
❌ No mobile-responsive design
❌ No self-registration for doctors (hardcoded users.json)

8.3 CLINICAL IMPLICATIONS
- Decision support tool (NOT replacement for medical judgment)
- Explainable AI builds trust with healthcare professionals
- Batch processing enables screening programs
- PDF reports integrate with clinical workflows
- Early detection can significantly improve patient outcomes
- Feature importance helps doctors understand model decisions

8.4 TECHNICAL INSIGHTS
- Random Forest excels due to ensemble nature (reduces overfitting)
- Feature scaling critical for SVM performance (+5% accuracy)
- Mean imputation preserves dataset integrity (+1% accuracy)
- 10-fold CV provides robust evaluation with limited data
- Feature importance helps doctors interpret predictions
- Session state works well for single-user demo (not multi-user)

